The paper addresses the problem of learning vector representations for entities and relations in Knowledge Graphs (KGs) for Knowledge Base Completion (KBC), which is a problem that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely sub-category as the paper proposes a neural network-based approach for learning representations of KGs, which is a common technique in AI research. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper involves learning representations using a neural network, which is a common technique in machine learning research. 

cs.CL (Computation and Language) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as knowledge base completion. 

cs.DB (Databases) is a relevant sub-category as the paper deals with knowledge graphs, which are a type of database. 

cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possible sub-category as the paper deals with evaluating the correctness of KG triples, which is a task that is relevant to information retrieval.
